imports in the pytest code. 

A command list is in the file: pytest_commands_to_run_from_HERE


The pytest code is located in this directory:
/home/ubuntu/course11_devops_startup_gitlab_repo/python_testing/AWS_infra_git_repo_env_MULTIPLE_USE/tests

The latest (current) version is: test_ai_hook_v7.py


conftest.py establishes the directory above as the root so that there are no import issues when running the pytest tests:
module2f is nested and has nested functions that will be problematic otherwise.
The monkeypatching is done to the SSH connection part of the code in module2f, as well as the AI/MCP hook returning the LLM
plan code in module2f.   The fakeSSH and fakeSSHv2 and the fake plan monkeypatching worked extremely well and many code 
permuations have been verifed. A key part of the testing was to validate the registry_entrys with pseudo pytest 
registry_entrys. The ai_metatdata fields and the ai_tags fields were all verifed as part of this whitebox testing to facilitate
the transition from whitebox testing to real-world testing in Phase4a.1.3.
